## Step 5 — SMS rate limiting (Twilio charges per SMS)

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class SmsWorker {

    private final TwilioClient twilio;
    private final RateLimiter smsRateLimiter;
    private final DeliveryStatusService statusService;

    @Bean
    public RateLimiter smsRateLimiter() {
        // External: Twilio allows max 100 SMS/sec on paid plan
        return RateLimiter.create(80.0);  // stay 20% below limit for safety
    }

    @KafkaListener(topics = "notifications.sms", groupId = "sms-workers")
    public void send(NotificationEvent event) {
        // Block until rate limit allows (prevents Twilio 429)
        smsRateLimiter.acquire();  // from Guava, thread-safe token bucket

        String phoneNumber = event.getPayload().get("phone");
        String message = renderTemplate(event.getTemplateId(), event.getPayload());

        twilio.send(phoneNumber, message);
        statusService.markDelivered(event.getId(), "sms", phoneNumber);
    }
}
```

