## Your interview answer

> "I separated the problem into two layers. For north-south (client to services), I added Spring Cloud Gateway: centralized JWT validation so no individual service does it anymore, rate limiting with Redis, and request logging with correlation IDs. Each service just reads the X-User-Id header the gateway sets. For east-west (service to service), I enabled Istio in the production namespace. All pods get an Envoy sidecar automatically — mTLS between services is enforced at the proxy level without any code changes. New services now just need to be registered as a route in the gateway config — the auth, rate limiting, and mTLS are inherited for free."

## The problem

```text
3 pods all start at midnight:
  Pod-1: @Scheduled(cron="0 0 0 1 * *") → triggers sendMonthlyInvoices()
  Pod-2: @Scheduled(cron="0 0 0 1 * *") → triggers sendMonthlyInvoices()
  Pod-3: @Scheduled(cron="0 0 0 1 * *") → triggers sendMonthlyInvoices()

All 3 run simultaneously → 3 invoices per customer

@Scheduled has no distributed awareness — each JVM runs independently.
```

---

## The fix — ShedLock (database-backed distributed lock)

### Step 1: Add dependency

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>net.javacrumbs.shedlock</groupId>
  <artifactId>shedlock-spring</artifactId>
  <version>5.10.0</version>
</dependency>
<dependency>
  <groupId>net.javacrumbs.shedlock</groupId>
  <artifactId>shedlock-provider-jdbc-template</artifactId>
  <version>5.10.0</version>
</dependency>
```

### Step 2: Create lock table in DB

```sql
CREATE TABLE shedlock (
    name       VARCHAR(64)  NOT NULL,
    lock_until TIMESTAMP(3) NOT NULL,
    locked_at  TIMESTAMP(3) NOT NULL,
    locked_by  VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (name)
);
```

**How ShedLock works:**
```text
All 3 pods try to INSERT into shedlock at the same time.
Only one succeeds (DB PRIMARY KEY constraint).
The other 2 see INSERT failure → skip execution.
Winner runs the job, then releases the lock (lock_until reset).
```

### Step 3: Configure ShedLock

```java
@Configuration
@EnableSchedulerLock(defaultLockAtMostFor = "10m")
public class SchedulerConfig {

    @Bean
    public LockProvider lockProvider(DataSource dataSource) {
        return new JdbcTemplateLockProvider(
            JdbcTemplateLockProvider.Configuration.builder()
                .withJdbcTemplate(new JdbcTemplate(dataSource))
                .usingDbTime()  // use DB time, not JVM time (prevents clock skew issues)
                .build()
        );
    }
}
```

### Step 4: Annotate your scheduled job

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Slf4j
public class BillingJobService {

    private final InvoiceService invoiceService;
    private final CustomerRepository customerRepo;

    @Scheduled(cron = "0 0 0 1 * *")  // 1st of every month at midnight
    @SchedulerLock(
        name = "monthly-billing-job",  // lock name — must be unique per job
        lockAtMostFor  = "30m",  // release lock after 30 min even if JVM crashes
        lockAtLeastFor = "5m"    // hold lock for min 5 min to prevent fast re-execution
    )
    public void sendMonthlyInvoices() {
        log.info("[BILLING] Starting monthly invoice job on instance: {}",
            InetAddress.getLocalHost().getHostName());

        List<Customer> customers = customerRepo.findAllActive();
        log.info("[BILLING] Processing {} customers", customers.size());

        int success = 0, failed = 0;
        for (Customer customer : customers) {
            try {
                invoiceService.generateAndSendInvoice(customer);
                success++;
            } catch (Exception e) {
                log.error("[BILLING] Failed for customer {}: {}", customer.getId(), e.getMessage());
                failed++;
            }
        }

        log.info("[BILLING] Completed. Success: {}, Failed: {}", success, failed);
    }
}
```

**What happens now with 3 pods:**

```text
00:00:00.000 - Pod-1 acquires lock → starts job
              INSERT INTO shedlock SET name='monthly-billing-job', locked_by='pod-1',
              lock_until=NOW()+30m → SUCCESS

00:00:00.003 - Pod-2 tries to acquire lock
              INSERT INTO shedlock SET name='monthly-billing-job', locked_by='pod-2'
              → FAILS (duplicate primary key 'monthly-billing-job')
              → Pod-2 SKIPS this execution

00:00:00.005 - Pod-3 tries to acquire lock
              → FAILS same way → Pod-3 SKIPS

00:14:23.000 - Pod-1 finishes → ShedLock releases the lock
              (or lock auto-releases at 00:30:00 if Pod-1 crashed)
```

**Log output showing single execution:**
```text
[pod-1] [BILLING] Starting monthly invoice job on instance: order-service-pod-1
[pod-1] [BILLING] Processing 4500 customers
[pod-1] [BILLING] Completed. Success: 4498, Failed: 2

[pod-2] (silence — lock not acquired, job skipped)
[pod-3] (silence — lock not acquired, job skipped)
```

