## Your interview answer

> "I wrapped the new checkout logic in a feature flag check using Unleash. The flag is configured with gradualRolloutUserId strategy at 10% — user ID is hashed consistently so the same user always sees the same experience. The old flow remains as the default. If error rates spike in Grafana, I log into Unleash, set rolloutPercentage to 0 — instant rollback in 0ms, no deployment. After 24 hours of monitoring at 10%, I increase to 25%, then 50%, then 100%. Once fully rolled out, I remove the flag code in the next sprint."

followUps.answer:
**1. Flag accumulation (flag debt):**
```text
Problem: You add a flag, never remove it. 2 years later: 300 flags in your codebase.
Code has if/else for every flag → hard to understand, hard to test.

Fix: Add a ticket to remove the flag when rollout reaches 100%.
Track flag age: alert when flag is older than 90 days without being cleaned up.
```

**2. Testing complexity:**
```java
// If you have 5 flags, each with 2 states: 2^5 = 32 combinations to test!
// Limit: don't have more than 2-3 active flags at the same time
// Test: at least test flag=ON and flag=OFF for every flag
@ParameterizedTest
@ValueSource(booleans = {true, false})
void checkoutWorksWithAndWithoutFlag(boolean newCheckoutEnabled) {
    when(unleash.isEnabled("new-checkout-flow", any())).thenReturn(newCheckoutEnabled);
    assertDoesNotThrow(() -> checkoutService.processCheckout(request, 1L));
}
```

**3. Inconsistent behavior within a session:**
```text
User adds item with new checkout (flag=ON)
User's next request hits different pod where flag is sampled differently
User suddenly sees old checkout — confused

Fix: Sticky sessions OR deterministic flag evaluation (userId % 100 always gives same result)
```

**4. Database migrations tied to flags:**
```text
Don't: Add a DB column that only new-checkout-flow reads
→ If flag is rolled back, old code might fail on the new column

Fix: DB migrations must be backward compatible — new columns must have defaults
→ Deploy DB migration FIRST, then code, then enable flag
```

**5. Performance overhead:**
```java
// Every request calls unleash.isEnabled() — which polls the API server
// Unleash SDK caches flags locally and refreshes every 15s — negligible
// For simple cases, check caches flags in memory — O(1) lookup
```

A/B testing with feature flags assigns users to variants deterministically and measures business metrics per variant.

**Setup — two variants:**
```java
// Unleash variant configuration
UnleashContext context = UnleashContext.builder()
    .userId(userId.toString())
    .build();

Variant variant = unleash.getVariant("checkout-ab-test", context);
// Returns: variant.getName() = "A" or "B" (configured in Unleash)

public CheckoutResult processCheckout(CheckoutRequest request, Long userId) {
    String variant = unleash.getVariant("checkout-ab-test", context).getName();

    // Track variant assignment
    analyticsService.trackExperiment(userId, "checkout-ab-test", variant);

    return switch (variant) {
        case "A" -> oldCheckout.process(request);       // control
        case "B" -> newCheckout.process(request);       // treatment
        default  -> oldCheckout.process(request);       // default
    };
}
```

**Key metrics to track per variant:**
```text
Conversion rate:   orders_completed / checkout_started per variant
Cart abandonment:  users who started checkout but didn't complete
Revenue per user:  total_revenue / unique_users per variant
Error rate:        500_errors / total_requests per variant
Latency P95:       95th percentile response time per variant

SQL report:
SELECT variant,
       COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) as users,
       COUNT(order_id) as completions,
       COUNT(order_id)::float / COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) as conversion_rate,
       AVG(order_amount) as avg_order_value
FROM checkout_events
WHERE experiment_name = 'checkout-ab-test'
GROUP BY variant;
```

**Statistical significance**: Need at least 1000 users per variant and 95% confidence before declaring a winner. Don't stop early just because one variant looks better after 100 users.

